cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Flock in academic work or a published project, please cite it as below."
title: "Flock: a self-hosted LLM gateway for multi-machine inference clusters"
abstract: |
  Flock is a Go-binary control plane that turns a fleet of Macs and Linux
  boxes into a private inference cluster behind a single OpenAI- and
  Anthropic-compatible endpoint. It ships a per-user API key system with
  daily quotas and a full audit log, multi-node routing with sharding via
  llama.cpp-RPC, transparent fallback to paid Claude / GPT / Bedrock /
  Vertex, an embedded admin dashboard, and Prometheus + OTLP
  observability. The runtime is engine-agnostic — Ollama, vLLM, MLX-LM,
  and llama.cpp drivers ship out of the box.
type: software
